Subject: ISO register of algorithms.
Message-ID: <1992Jan24.090153.25993@apricot.co.uk>
Date: 24 Jan 92 09:01:53 GMT
Organization: Apricot Computers Limited
Lines: 43

I have read [1] that ISO were, at one stage, going to start a register
of cryptographic algorithms with the following information for each
entry:

..."
a) a formal ISO-entry name for the algorithm
b) proprietary name, if any
c) intended range of use
d) cryptographic interface parameters (block size, key domain, etc.)
e) set of functional test words
f) identity of organisation requesting registration
g) dates of registration and modifications
h) whether subject of a national standard
i) patent licence restrictions
j) export restrictions
k) list of references to associated algorithms
m) statement of modes of operation
n) other information

"...

This register would make very interesting reading.  Does anybody have
a progress update on this one?

